title: Pair Of Covered Jars, 1740–50
description: Inverted acorn shaped with cavetto neck and domed cover with floral knob. Cylindrical foot; side broken by four vertical grooves alternating with four ridges. Floral festoons in relief on shoulders, flowers in relief upon covers, which have silver rims.

tombstone.epitaph: Pair Of Covered Jars, 1740–50. Soft-paste porcelain. 1921-25-1-a/d.
